List Available Groq Models

Source: R/chat-groq.R
models_groq.Rd

Retrieves a list of available models from the Groq API. Returns model metadata including context window size and active status.

Usage

models_groq(
  base_url = "https://api.groq.com/openai/v1",
  api_key = NULL,
  credentials = NULL
)

Arguments

base_url

Base URL for the Groq API.

api_key

Use credentials instead.

credentials

Override the default credentials. You generally should not need this argument; instead set the GROQ_API_KEY environment variable.

Value

A data frame with columns:

id

Model identifier (e.g., "llama-3.3-70b-versatile")

created_at

Date the model was created

owned_by

Organization that owns/provides the model

context_window

Maximum context window size in tokens

active

Whether the model is currently active/available

See also

chat_groq_developer() for creating chat sessions

Examples

if (FALSE) { # \dontrun{
# List all available models
models <- models_groq()
print(models)

# Filter for active models with large context windows
large_context <- models[models$context_window >= 32768 & models$active, ]
} # }
